rComments: An engaging and insightful lecturer. His teaching technique is to capture interest and allow his students to think creatively rather than systematically. In this respect it's perfect for engineering. Just like the classical music he plays prior to class, his lecture style flies right over the heads of those who don't aspire to be engaged thinkers.

Completely out of touch with the class, provides about 50x more detail than needed (or wanted) considering that 75% of the class will not work in this specific field. This class needs a major overhaul.
he is quite the aragent person. He may know alot but expects u to know a lot in return. Not the best person to go for when u need help
